Within 24 hours of collection, her urine culture becomes positive for >100,000 CFU/mL of a gram-negative bacillus.  The organism is identified as Escherichia coli, confirming a diagnosis of E. coli urosepsis.  The isolate is susceptible to all antibiotics tested, including ceftriaxone.  The patientâ€™s blood culture becomes positive for E. coli, as well.  

